<ServicePage
  title="Dental Bonding in Bayside, Queens NY | Thrive Dental"
  description="Dental bonding in Bayside, Queens NY to repair chipped, cracked, or discolored teeth. Fast, affordable, and natural-looking results in a single visit. Call (718) 225-6677."
  category="Cosmetic Dentistry"
  categoryHref="/services/cosmetic-dentistry"
  h1="Dental Bonding in Bayside, NY"
  subtitle="Dental bonding is one of the most versatile and affordable cosmetic treatments available. Fix chips, cracks, gaps, and discoloration in a single visit with tooth-colored composite resin."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  heroImgPosition="45%"
  overviewTitle="Cosmetic fixes. One appointment."
  overviewText="Dental bonding uses a tooth-colored composite resin — the same material used for modern fillings — that is applied directly to the tooth, sculpted into shape, and hardened with a curing light. The process requires no drilling in most cases, no anesthesia, and no lab fabrication, which means you walk in with the problem and walk out with it resolved. An experienced cosmetic dentist can achieve results with bonding that are genuinely beautiful — closing gaps, reshaping irregular edges, and covering stains in a way that looks completely natural."
  overviewExtra="For patients in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who want cosmetic improvements without the commitment or cost of veneers, dental bonding is often the ideal starting point. At Thrive Dental, we use a multi-shade composite system that allows us to mimic the subtle color variations of natural tooth enamel — so bonded teeth don't have the flat, artificial look that lower-quality composites can produce. Same-day bonding appointments are available most days of the week. If you have a chipped front tooth, uneven edges, a small gap, or a tooth that's darker than the rest, call us — bonding may be a one-visit solution."
  benefits={[
    {
      icon: `<rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/>`,
      title: 'Single-Visit Results',
      desc: 'No lab, no temporary restorations, no waiting. Most bonding cases are completed in one appointment, start to finish.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>`,
      title: 'Preserves Tooth Structure',
      desc: 'Unlike veneers, bonding requires little to no enamel removal. The natural tooth stays largely intact.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"/>`,
      title: 'Versatile',
      desc: 'Chips, cracks, gaps, discoloration, short teeth, exposed roots — bonding addresses a wider range of cosmetic concerns than almost any other single treatment.',
    },
  ]}
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'What can dental bonding fix?',
      a: 'Bonding can repair chipped or cracked teeth, close small gaps, cover stains that won\'t whiten, reshape uneven or short teeth, and protect exposed tooth roots from sensitivity.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How long does dental bonding last?',
      a: 'Composite bonding typically lasts 5–10 years with proper care. Bonding can chip if you bite nails or chew ice. We can touch it up easily at a routine visit.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Is bonding as good as veneers?',
      a: 'Bonding is faster and more affordable, but porcelain veneers are more stain-resistant and durable. For minor cosmetic issues, bonding is an excellent solution. For a comprehensive smile makeover, veneers may be the better long-term investment.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Does dental bonding hurt?',
      a: 'For most applications, dental bonding requires no anesthesia and is completely painless.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Will bonding stain over time?',
      a: 'Composite resin can pick up staining from coffee, tea, and red wine over time. Regular cleanings help maintain the color. If the bonding becomes discolored, we can polish or replace it.',
    },
  ]}
